Privacy Policy for Mobile Tester

Last updated: April 18, 2025

Mobile Tester ("the App") is a learning application for mobile QA engineers
developed by Vladislav Kazachek.

1. INFORMATION WE COLLECT

The App does not collect, store, or transmit any personal information.
We do not require account registration or login.

2. DATA STORED LOCALLY

The App stores the following data exclusively on your device:
- Your quiz progress and results
- Achievements you have earned
- Your language preference (Russian or English)
- Notification reminder settings

This data never leaves your device and is not accessible to us.

3. INTERNET ACCESS

The App connects to the internet solely to load the following content
from our public GitHub repository (github.com/Vladislav-Mobile/app):
- Author articles
- Podcast episodes

No personal data is sent during these requests.

4. LOCAL NOTIFICATIONS

The App may send local notifications as reminders if you choose to
enable them. These notifications are generated entirely on your device
and do not involve any external servers.

5. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES

The App does not use any third-party analytics, advertising SDKs,
or tracking services.

6. CHILDREN'S PRIVACY

The App does not knowingly collect any information from children
under the age of 13.

7. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will
be posted at this location.

8. CONTACT

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact:
